records.addlTxt:
11:29 AM Judge Mary Burns mentoring with Judge Neal Nielsen. Defendant Ryan D. Sisco appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek appeared by video for Ryan D. Sisco.  Attorney Michael Schiek in court for State of Wisconsin. Plea Questionnaire and Waiver filed in 22CF134. Calling 21CM232, 21CF338, 22CF134, 22CF29. Schiek statement-speaks to global agreement/joint resolution. State moves to dismiss and read in 21CF338, 22CF29, 21CM232; granted. Svehlek statement/defendant waives preliminary hearing in 22CF134. Court finds waiver free and voluntary; finds that probable cause exists and binds over. Defendant pleads no contest to both counts in 22CF134. Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea; waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Defendant waives right to appear in person for plea/sentencing. Schiek/Svehlek/Sisco statement to sentencing. Court statement to sentencing. adj. 11:56 a.m.

Court sentence - 22CF134; 
WHS; 
3 yrs. POP; 
4 mos. conditional jail w/Huber; 
Jail credit 14 days, if revoked;  
CC only;
Restitution $60.50 in 21CM232 (collected by DOC), includes surcharge;
DNA sample; 
The court informs defendant of right to request expungement of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4). 
Voter Ineligibility Notice given. 
Appeal rights given.
